The National Drug Law Enforcement Agency (NDLEA) has intercepted a container with 4,996,200 capsules of tramadol weighing 2,498kg at the Onne Port, Port Harcourt, Rivers State. The spokesman, Femi Babafemi in a statement said the illicit drug was concealed in 1,387 cartons. The discovery followed a joint examination by NDLEA operatives and Customs personnel on a container marked MRKU 0764717. The agency disclosed that the consignment had been on the agencyâ€™s watch list. However, Muntari Hamidu, 42, was arrested in the Nyibango area of Jimeta in Yola, Adamawa, with 13 sacks of cannabis sativa weighing 166kg. Similarly, Sani Musa, 35, was apprehended with16.1kg of skunk at Ngurore, Yola South Local Government Area (LAG) of the state. In Ondo, operatives nabbed James Godspower with 36.5kg of cannabis sativa in Faloye, Ogbese, Akure North LGA of Ondo State. NDLEA Chairman, Brig. General Mohamed Buba Marwa (rtd) commended the Rivers, Adamawa and Ondo Commands for their resilience and commitment. NDLEA seeks establishment of drugs laboratories across Nigeria 